  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/6272",
  "title": "React-Instantsearch Typescript, hits is depreciated on 7.12.0",
  "body": "### 🐛 Current behavior\n\nCurrently, I am using the following code:\r\n\r\n```\r\nconst { hits } = useInfiniteHits<MyType>();\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis is giving me an error inside of VSCode stating that hits is depreciated.\r\n\r\nReverting to 7.11.0 resolves the issue, however I end up running into typing problems as seen and described in https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/5989\r\n\r\nDoing some digging, it is asking me to use ```items``` instead of ```hits```, however this is not described in the InfiniteHits hook description seen here:\r\n\r\nhttps://www.algolia.com/doc/api-reference/widgets/infinite-hits/react/\r\n\r\nCan we the change of depreciating {hits} from useInfiniteHits() be removed from 7.12.0 until the documentation is properly updated?\n\n### 🔍 Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Install TypeScript\r\n2. npm install algoliasearch react-instantsearch\r\n\r\nCauses this issue in VSCode.\n\n### Live reproduction\n\nN/A\n\n### 💭 Expected behavior\n\nEither the keys for the hooks should match the documentation, or hits should be depreciated\n\n### Package version\n\nalgoliasearch@latest, react-instantsearch@7.12.0\n\n### Operating system\n\nWindows 11\n\n### Browser\n\nChrome\n\n### Code of Conduct\n\n- [X] I agree to follow this project's Code of Conduct",
